A MALE nurse has been bust after the body of Naledi Chaka (4) was found in a pit toilet, not far from her home, on Thursday night. The child from Selosesha in Thaba Nchu, Free State, went missing last Sunday. One of the kids who were playing with the victim told cops Naledi was last seen with a male suspect. Police went to the suspect’s house in Selosesha zone 2 and found the body inside the pit toilet. Daily Sun visited the family. They were still shocked and couldn’t speak to the SunTeam. Police spokesman Sergeant Martin Xuma told the People’s Paper: “A 36-year-old male nurse was arrested and is expected to appear in the Thaba Nchu Magistrates Court soon on charges of kidnapping and murder. “This follows the discovery of some of the victims’s clothes on Wednesday. They were found on the street, not far from her home.” Xuma said that fire and rescue teams were called to the scene and they retrieved the body. “A post mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death, and whether the victim was raped or not,” said Xuma. Provincial polive commissioner Lieutenant-General Moeketsi Sempe condemned the killing of the little girl. He urged the investigating officers to use all available resources to ensure justice is served.